HEADWORD: Hornito
<hw>Hor*ni"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A dim. fr. Sp.
<ets>horno</ets> oven, L. <ets>furnus</ets>. See
<er>Furnace</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A low, oven-shaped
mound, common in volcanic regions, and emitting smoke and vapors from
its sides and summit.</def> <rj><au>Humboldt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornless</ent>⟦br⟧
